'''''thôl''''' is a [[Sindarin]] word, meaning "helm"<ref>{{S|Appendix}}, ''thôl''</ref> or "helmet". Plural forms were ''thely'', ''thuil''.<ref>{{PE|17}}, pp. 186, 188</ref> 

==Examples==
* ''[[Dor-Cúarthol|Dor-Cúar'''thol''']]'' = "Land of Bow and Helm"
* ''[[Castol|cas'''tol''']]'' = "helmet"
* ''[[Gorthol|Gor'''thol''']]'' = "Dread Helm"

